# Review of `app.js` — Error Handling & Input Validation

The file is a minimal Express app (~22 lines). There's no user input being accepted yet and no error handling anywhere, so most of my suggestions are preventative hardening for when the surface area grows. Below is a prioritized list.

## 1. Missing global error handling

There is no error-handling middleware and no handler for uncaught exceptions or unhandled promise rejections. A thrown error in any route will currently crash the process or leak stack traces.

**Recommend:**
