### 4. No input validation scaffolding
There are no parameterized routes yet, but when you add them (e.g. `/users/:id`), validate input at the boundary with a schema library (`zod`, `joi`, or `express-validator`) rather than ad-hoc checks. Reject unknown fields, coerce types explicitly, and never pass `req.query`/`req.body`/`req.params` straight to a DB driver or shell.

### 5. Hardcoded port & no graceful shutdown
```js
