## Current issues

### 1. No global error handling
Express won't catch async errors by default, and there's no error-handling middleware. Any unexpected throw will leak stack traces or crash the process.

### 2. No request validation / body parsing hardening
Although the current routes don't read input, the app has no `express.json()` limits, no schema validation library, and no route-level input validation — this becomes dangerous the moment input-accepting endpoints are added.

