| Concern | Recommendation |
|---|---|
| **HTTP headers** | Use `helmet()` to set `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`, CSP, etc. Disable `X-Powered-By`. |
| **CORS** | Never use `cors()` with defaults in production — specify an explicit origin allowlist via env var. |
| **Body size** | Always set a `limit` on `express.json()` / `express.urlencoded()` to prevent memory-exhaustion DoS. |
| **Rate limiting** | Use `express-rate-limit` at minimum; consider `express-slow-down` or a Redis-backed limiter behind a proxy. |
| **Input validation** | Use `express-validator` or `zod`/`joi` schemas on every route that accepts input. Validate `params`, `query`, and `body`. Reject unknown fields. |
| **Async errors** | Wrap async handlers (or use Express 5, which handles rejected promises natively). Without this, rejected promises crash silently. |
| **Error responses** | Return generic messages for 5xx; never return raw `err.message` or stack traces to clients. Log the full error server-side. |
| **Logging** | Replace `console.log` with `pino` or `winston`; add `pino-http` / `morgan` for request logs; include request IDs. |
| **Secrets/config** | Load from environment variables (use `dotenv` in dev). Never hardcode credentials or ports for production. |
| **Testability** | Guard `app.listen` behind `require.main === module` so `require('./app')` in tests doesn't bind a port. |
| **Dependency hygiene** | Run `npm audit` in CI; pin versions; enable Dependabot. |
| **TLS** | Terminate TLS at a reverse proxy (nginx, ALB) and trust the proxy with `app.set('trust proxy', 1)` so rate limiting and IP logging work correctly. |
| **Auth** (when added) | Use well-tested middleware (`passport`, JWT with short expiry + refresh, or session cookies with `Secure`, `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Strict`). Never roll your own. |
| **SQL/NoSQL injection** (when added) | Use parameterized queries or an ORM. Never concatenate user input into queries. |

---

## Quick wins (if you only do three things)

1. **Add `helmet()` + disable `x-powered-by` + body size limit** — one-line changes, high impact.
2. **Add a centralized error handler and 404 handler** — prevents stack-trace leaks and unhandled promise rejections.
3. **Guard `app.listen` with `require.main === module`** — makes the file safely importable for tests.

